&lt;p>My first try at a renderer was using a guide provided by Tsoding in his project &lt;code>olive.c&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://github.com/tsoding/olive.c">olive.c&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>Using these basic concepts, I then used the tutorial provided by The Coding Train to render a mandelbrot fractal:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://thecodingtrain.com/challenges/21-mandelbrot-set-with-p5js">The Coding Train challenge: mandel brot set in p5.js&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;code>mandelbrot/&lt;/code> has my first c port. Afterwards, I tried parallelizing my renderer
using multithreading and openmp: &lt;code>mandelbrot-gamma/&lt;/code> &lt;code>mandelbrot-lambda/&lt;/code> &lt;del>is
in the works but it&amp;rsquo;s supposed to be the same as mandelbrot-gamma but using
lambdas&lt;/del> I will probably remove this further on since mandelbrot-gamma has
proven to be the way forward for this project.&lt;/p>
